    <item>
      <title>Composable Collectable</title>
      <link>/post/composable-collectable/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 14 Nov 2021 08:47:00 +0530</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/post/composable-collectable/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-container-headline-1&#34; class=&#34;outline-2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;headline-1&#34;&gt;
What is composable collectable?
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-text-headline-1&#34; class=&#34;outline-text-2&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
If you are not familiar with with collectable checkout about it
HexDocs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&amp;gt; If the functions in Enumerable are about taking values out, then Collectable.into/1 is about collecting those values into a structure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Another way of thinking about these is that Enumerable helps with
the act of pulling values out of something. And Collectable helps with
the act of pushing values into a something. In both of these case
We don&amp;#39;t really care what implementation details of that &amp;#34;the something&amp;#34;.
The protocols are about the act of pulling and pushing. The something might be
a list, map, tcp connection or file on disk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-container-headline-2&#34; class=&#34;outline-2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;headline-2&#34;&gt;
Why we need collectable to be composable?
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-text-headline-2&#34; class=&#34;outline-text-2&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
For the same reason why we need `Enum` and `Stream` module to work with Enumerable.
Currently there is no equivalent modules to compose Collectable values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Let&amp;#39;s take an example and see&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
You have infinite stream of logs, each line in stream can be of
different level – info, warn, error. The task is that you want to
push logs to somewhere. And this somewhere is unknown and should be
configurable. You might want to push all logs to s3 or push to a
file. or push error logs to console and skip remaining (push to void).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
How would you model this keeping the flexibility in mind? Assume that
flexibility part of the requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Cases like these are why and hopefully at the end of the post we solve
this better using composable collectable, and convince you about the
usefulness of it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-container-headline-3&#34; class=&#34;outline-2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;headline-3&#34;&gt;
Push Containers
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-text-headline-3&#34; class=&#34;outline-text-2&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
To avoid getting lost in the details of Collection protocol. Which
just a one way to represent push container. Lets build our own push
contianer in a bottom-up approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
So we want something where we can push stuff. We don&amp;#39;t care about implementation
details of something.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Lets build this using functions. So the contract is – we call `push` function with
the something as first argument and the thing we want to push as second
argument. So if something wants to a push container it only has to
implement `push(something, anything)` function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# string container&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; push(string, value) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;when&lt;/span&gt; is_binary(string) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  string &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; value
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# list container&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; push(list, value) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;when&lt;/span&gt; is_list(list) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  list &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;++&lt;/span&gt; [value]
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# void container&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; push(nil, _) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  nil
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Lets see how this can be used&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; generate_strings(container, count) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  chars &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;?a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;?g&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;reduce(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;..&lt;/span&gt;count, container, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; _, container &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    string &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; to_string(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;shuffle(chars))
    push(container, string)
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;


&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Foo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;generate_strings(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;|&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;IO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;inspect(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;label&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;string&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Foo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;generate_strings([], &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;|&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;IO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;inspect(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;label&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;list&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Foo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;generate_strings(nil, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;|&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;IO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;inspect(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;label&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;nil&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Push container does not have to be a data strucutre like list, string
It can be a process, socket or file. For resource like push container
We also need a way to initialise this and and release it. For example
for file initialise step which is opening the file and release step might
be closing the file. While at it lets group all these 3 functions into
a module so it is easier to build container for different type.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;defmodule&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;defstruct&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:acc&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:init&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:func&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:finish&lt;/span&gt;]

  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; build(init, func, finish) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
    %__MODULE__{&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;init&lt;/span&gt;: init &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;func&lt;/span&gt;: func, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;finish&lt;/span&gt;: finish}
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; init(%&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;init&lt;/span&gt;: init} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; pc) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
    %&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;{pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;acc&lt;/span&gt;: init&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;(), &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;init&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:done&lt;/span&gt;}
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; push(%&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;acc&lt;/span&gt;: acc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;push&lt;/span&gt;: push} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; pc, value) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
    %&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;{pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;acc&lt;/span&gt;: push&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;(acc, value)}
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; push(%&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;acc&lt;/span&gt;: acc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;finish&lt;/span&gt;: finish} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; pc) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
    finish&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;(acc)
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# Lets make changes to generate strings to adopt to new interface&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; generate_strings(%&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;{} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; pc, count) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  chars &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;?a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;?g&lt;/span&gt;

  pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;init(pc)

  pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;reduce(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;..&lt;/span&gt;count, pc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; _, container &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
      string &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; to_string(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;shuffle(chars))
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;push(pc, string)
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;)

  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;finish(pc)
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Lets build push containers using new interface&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;
string_pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;build(
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; acc, val &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; acc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; str &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; acc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; acc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
  )

list_pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;build(
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; [] &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; acc, val &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; acc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;++&lt;/span&gt; [val] &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; acc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; acc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
  )

file_pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;build(
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;File&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;open!(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;somefile.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; file, val &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;IO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;binwrite!(file, val) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; file &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;File&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;close(file) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
  )


str &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; generate_string(string_pc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;)
list &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; generate_string(list_pc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:ok&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; generate_string(file_pc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Now that we have different push containers. Let&amp;#39;s head back to
composability aspect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-container-headline-4&#34; class=&#34;outline-2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;headline-4&#34;&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;priority&#34;&gt;[C]&lt;/span&gt;
Composing push containers
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-text-headline-4&#34; class=&#34;outline-text-2&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
In the case above when we call &lt;code&gt;generate_string(..., 1000)&lt;/code&gt;
we are pushing string to the container. Now say we also want to
upcase the string before we push. How to do this while keeping
existing code intact?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Lets create a function which wraps &lt;code&gt;func&lt;/code&gt; with the given function.
It is same as &lt;code&gt;Enum.map&lt;/code&gt; but for push-container. Basically
we need to create a new push container which wraps the passed
container using the wrapper function passed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;@spec&lt;/span&gt; map((any &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; any), &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;t()) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;t()
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; map(%&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;{} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; pc, func) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;build(
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;init(pc) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; acc, elem &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;push(pc, func&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;(elem)) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; acc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;finish(pc) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
  )
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

string &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
  generate_strings(
    map(string_pc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;upcase&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;),
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;
  )

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# string -&amp;gt; upcase -&amp;gt; encode64 -&amp;gt; create-string&lt;/span&gt;
string &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
  generate_strings(
    map(
      map(
        string_pc,
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Base&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;encode64&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
      ),
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;upcase&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
    ),
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;
  )&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
This works but as you can see in the last example it not easy to read.
It is even worse if we write it in single line&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;generate_strings(map(map(string_pc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Base&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;encode64&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;), &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;upcase&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;), &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;)

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# for comparison, how something similar would look using Enum&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# Enum.map(Enum.map(generate_strings(10), &amp;amp;String.upcase/1), &amp;amp;Base.encode64/1)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
What is the issue here?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
The issue is that we are trained to read code top-to-bottom. Because
that&amp;#39;s how most programming languages model control flow. It is hard
to simulate operation execution if this is not true. This why in
Elixir we have pipe operator &lt;code&gt;|&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; which is basically a macro-magic we
use to trick our brain. This makes chaining &lt;code&gt;Enum&lt;/code&gt; more readable. This
works because in case of Enum because first argument is essentially
&amp;#34;input&amp;#34; in case of the enum. The input values are pulled from the first
argument, that is line before pipe which makes movement of values seem
natural - top-to-bottom.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;map(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;map(generate_strings(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;), &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;upcase&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;), &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Base&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;encode64&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# using pipe it becomes&lt;/span&gt;

generate_strings(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;|&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;map(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;upcase&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;|&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;map(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Base&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;encode64&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
It is more obvious if we visualise the way we read the code&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../../assets/enum-left-to-right/image.gif&#34; alt=&#34;../../assets/enum-left-to-right/image.gif&#34; title=&#34;../../assets/enum-left-to-right/image.gif&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../../assets/enum-top-to-bottom/image.gif&#34; alt=&#34;../../assets/enum-top-to-bottom/image.gif&#34; title=&#34;../../assets/enum-top-to-bottom/image.gif&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
We can&amp;#39;t take advantage of the pipe for push-containers because a
push-container is not an input, it is where where operation push the
output. So using pipe for push container appear confusing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;generate_strings(map(map(string_pc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Base&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;encode64&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;), &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;upcase&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;), &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;)

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# using pipe becomes&lt;/span&gt;

string_pc
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;|&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; map(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Base&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;encode64&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;|&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; map(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;upcase&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;|&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; generate_strings(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
are good at reading (or parsing code) from
left to right, top to bottom. Because that&amp;#39;s how most languages are
structured and we are trained.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Let&amp;#39;s implement few more basic operations and bundle them as Coll,
sort of Collectors, similar to Enum is for Enumerable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Coll&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; reduce(func, %&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;{} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; pc) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;init(pc)
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; elem, pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        func&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;(elem, pc)
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;finish(pc)
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
    )
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# let&amp;#39;s simplify map using reduce&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; map(func, %&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;{} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; pc) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
    reduce(
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; elem, pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;call(pc, func&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;(elem))
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
      pc
    )
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; filter(func, %&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;{} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; pc) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
    reduce(
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; elem, pc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; func&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;(elem) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
          &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;PushContainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;call(pc, elem)
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
          pc
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
      pc
    )
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Equipped with these functions we can compose them however we want&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; format_string(label, collect) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Coll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;map(
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; str &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;#{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;DateTime&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;utc_now()&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt; : &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;#{&lt;/span&gt;str&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    collect
  )
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

list &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
  generate_strings(
    format_string(list_collect())
  )

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# filter strings with length &amp;gt; 3 and write upcase of those strings&lt;/span&gt;
string &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
  generate_strings(
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Coll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;filter(
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; str &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;length(str) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Coll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;map(
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; str &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;upcase(str) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
        string_collect()
      )
    )
  )
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# =&amp;gt; &amp;#34;FOO BAR&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
All our functiosn works with &lt;code&gt;Collect&lt;/code&gt; type but since elixir already
provides &lt;code&gt;Collectable&lt;/code&gt; protocol and many types and different libraries
already implement it. All we need now is just to bridge the &lt;code&gt;Collect&lt;/code&gt;
and &lt;code&gt;Collectable&lt;/code&gt; protocol for interoperability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; from_collectable(collectable) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Collect&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Collectable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;into(collectable)
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; {acc, collector_func}, elem &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
      collector_func&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;(acc, {&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:cont&lt;/span&gt;, elem})
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; {acc, collector_func}, status &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
      collector_func&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;(acc, status)
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
  )
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;defimpl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Collectable&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Collect&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; into(%&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Collect&lt;/span&gt;{} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; collect) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
    collector_func &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt;
      acc, {&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:cont&lt;/span&gt;, elem} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Collect&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;call(acc, elem)

      acc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:halt&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Collect&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;finish(acc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:halt&lt;/span&gt;)

      acc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:done&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Collect&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;finish(acc, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:done&lt;/span&gt;)
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;

    acc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Collect&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;init(collect)
    {acc, collector_func}
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Example&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;mapset &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;into(
    [&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;],
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Coll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;map(
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; num &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; num &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#bd93f9&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Coll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;from_collectable(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;MapSet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new())
    )
  )


&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;# =&amp;gt; [2, 4, 6, 8 ...]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
And for the original example problem, we set out to solve. Which is how
to split stream of logs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;src src-elixir&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-elixir&#34; data-lang=&#34;elixir&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;:ok&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
  write_logs(
    stream,
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Coll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;filter(
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; str &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;start_with?(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;foo:&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;,
      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;Coll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;from_collectable(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#50fa7b&#34;&gt;File&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;stream!(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;foo.log&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;))
    )
  )&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
